   - One region completely contains the other

   Mathematically, two regions [src, src+src_len) and [dst, dst+dst_len) overlap if:
   - src < dst + dst_len AND dst < src + src_len

   Or in simpler terms:
   - The maximum of the two start addresses is less than the minimum of the two end addresses

